. Hi, you can use columns or a table for this.
So you define two columns (first auto-sized for the image, and second - star-sized to use the rest of available width).
The only problem is, that setting the second column's width would interfere with image-width settings, so you'll need an artificial element (like a stack), wrapping the image:
js
columns: [
    {
        width: 'auto',
        // normally you could put image directly here, but since you're
        // setting width to auto, we need an artificial wrapping-node
        // so that column-width does not interfere with image width
        stack: [
            {
                image: 'data:image/jpg;base64 (...)'
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        alignment: 'center',
        text: 'Your header'
    }
]
Here you go with an example which you can paste directly to Playground - logo has low quality (I've taken a screenshot)
```
// playground requires you to assign document definition to a variable called dd
var dd = {
    content: [
        {
            columns: [
                {
                    width: 'auto',
                    stack: [
                        {
                            image: 'data:image/jpg;base64,)'
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    width: '*',
                    alignment: 'center',
                    stack: [
                        {
                            style: 'h1',
                            text: 'Comision Reguladora de Energia'
                        },
                        {
                            style: 'h2',
                            text: 'ACUSE DE RECIBO'
                        },
                        {
                            style: 'h2',
                            text: 'Envio de Correspondencia Digital'
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    styles: {
        h1: {
            margin: [0, 30, 0, 0],
            fontSize: 16,
            bold: true
        },
        h2: {
            margin: [0, 5, 0, 0],
            fontSize: 10,
            bold: true
        }
    }
}
```
