Now I've been thinking about 2 types of extensions:
- transformations (which would basically "translate" one node type to another),
- custom node types - logically consisting of 3 methods:
measure - pdfmake would ask "given rectangle of this max-size, return me your min-max widths"
calculateLayout - pdfmake would say: "hey!, your width's X, now calculate your layout and use PageElementWriter to add appropriate structures to DocumentContext" (ElementWriter/PageElementWriter would need some kind of abstraction instead of Line/Vector/Image to let the plugin extend them as well)
render - this would be optional (and only used in case calculateLayout used a custom structure instead of standard Line/Vector/Image) and would give access to the underlying pdfkit
