If you use a string not interrupted by any spaces, the continuous string breaks the column layout and breaks the outer page margins. Here is a modified example from the playground that illustrates the issue (best viewed in the pdfmake playground, of course): 
```
// playground requires you to assign document definition to a variable called dd
var dd = {
  pageSize: 'LETTER',
  pageMargins: [ 72, 72, 72, 72 ],
  content: [
    { text: 'My Book Title', fontSize: 25 },
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    ' ',
    'About three inches below the very top of the page, we start writing a sentence. Does pdfmake provide a way to guarantee the measurement?',
    ' ',
    {
      columns: [
    { stack: [
        { text: 'first column is just this sentence with lines below. You can see there is an implicit line break when a sentence has spaces, but not when there is a continuous string of characters.' },
        { text: '____________________________________________________'},
        { text: '___________________________________'},
        { text: '___________________________________'}
      ]    
    },
    {
      stack: [
