vbuser2004:
Did you use npm to install pdfMake in your project? I did and created a pdf on the server (using nodejs), and the info metadata did not work as you described. However, when you look at the printer.js file on github it does apply metadata to file correctly (see link here: https://github.com/bpampuch/pdfmake/blob/master/src/printer.js).
Before I figured this out, I added this functionality myself in a bit different way. Here is just as a suggestion:
Change printer.js file to include:
//Check if metadate provided in document definition
    if (docDefinition.hasOwnProperty("info")){
        this.pdfKitDoc = createMetaData(docDefinition.info, this.pdfKitDoc);
    }else{
        //No info provided - enter Creator & Producer Only
        this.pdfKitDoc.info.Creator = 'pdfmake';
        this.pdfKitDoc.info.Producer = 'pdfmake';
    }
And then this function:
```
function createMetaData(info, pdfKitDoc){
//Assign values to document or null if no value present
pdfKitDoc.info.Author = info.author || null;
pdfKitDoc.info.Title = info.title || null;
pdfKitDoc.info.Subject = info.subject || null;
pdfKitDoc.info.Keywords = info.keywords || null;

//Assigns pdfmake if Creator or Producer not provided
pdfKitDoc.info.Creator = info.creator || 'pdfmake';
pdfKitDoc.info.Producer = info.producer || 'pdfmake';

//Assigns date or automatically inserts current date
pdfKitDoc.info.CreationDate = info.creationdate || new Date();
pdfKitDoc.info.ModDate = info.moddate || new Date();

return pdfKitDoc;

};
```
The matches the pdfMake documentation of keeping the metadata tags in lowercase in the 'info' section, though according to PDFKit the spec has these capitalized (camel case). It also maintains pdfmake as Creator and Producer if no metadata is provided.
Note that the CreationDate in pdfkit is off by one month. Check out this fix: https://github.com/devongovett/pdfkit/issues/447
Attached is the full suggested printer.js file. 
Good luck!
