tristantbg:
I found out where the problem was.
I was retrieving a footer with a different content at each page :
javascript
var docDefinition = {
    footer: function(currentPage) {
        return {
            text: standnumbers[currentPage - 1],
            alignment: 'center'
        };
    }
};
And when the script was doing the last page and obviously the last pageBreak, my array had no more value to create the very last blank page.
So by doing this the pdf is finally created :
javascript
var docDefinition = {
    footer: function(currentPage) {
        if (currentPage - 1 < standnumbers.length) {
            return {
                text: standnumbers[currentPage - 1],
                alignment: 'center'
            };
        } else {
            return {
                text: "END",
                alignment: 'center'
            };
        }
    }
}
